  "title": "Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES</strong>:</p><p>· Assist Accountant on month end closing, ensure accuracy and timely closure of monthly accounts</p><p>· Assist in reconciling progress claim for the month</p><p>· Assist AR in invoice issuance and credit control as required</p><p>· Oversea preparation of materials usage report.</p><p>· Ensure accurate data entry into ERP system with necessary supporting documents</p><p>· Timely uploading of monthly financials for Group reporting and compliance.</p><p>· Assist in balance sheet preparation.</p><p>· Assist in submission of audit and tax requirements for various Altrad entities.</p><p>· Any additional duties assigned as required.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Possess at least Diploma in Accountancy or equivalent with at least 2-3 years of relevant experience.</p><p>· Junior Executives specializing in GL/AR/AP Accounting</p><p>· Able to work effectively under pressure and meet tight deadlines.</p><p>· Experience in Accpac is highly desirable</p><p>· Reliable and responsible, shows attention to detail</p><p>· At least 2 years relevant experience in the same capacity, preferably in similar or related industries.</p><p>· Educational Qualifications: Degree / Diploma in Accounting</p><p>· Competent with Microsoft applications including Outlook, Word with advance excel skills</p><p>· Good communication skills.</p>",
